2026-02-15 | Add Two Binary Strings

	Question
Given binary strings a and b,
return their sum as a binary string.

	Approach
1.	We simulate binary addition from right to left.
2.	Initialize:
		i = last index of a
		j = last index of b
		carry = 0
3.	While i ≥ 0 OR j ≥ 0 OR carry > 0:
		sum = carry
		if i ≥ 0 → add (a[i] − '0')
		if j ≥ 0 → add (b[j] − '0')
		result digit = sum % 2
		carry = sum / 2
4.	Append result digit to a string.
5.	Reverse the result at the end.
6.	Time Complexity:
		O(max(n, m))
7.	Space Complexity:
		O(max(n, m))

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    string addBinary(string a, string b) {
        int i = a.size() - 1;
        int j = b.size() - 1;
        int carry = 0;
        string result = "";

        while (i >= 0 || j >= 0 || carry) {
            int sum = carry;

            if (i >= 0) {
                sum += a[i] - '0';
                i--;
            }

            if (j >= 0) {
                sum += b[j] - '0';
                j--;
            }

            result.push_back((sum % 2) + '0');
            carry = sum / 2;
        }

        reverse(result.begin(), result.end());
        return result;
    }
};

	Key Insight
This problem is simply manual binary addition.
Process digits from right to left while maintaining carry,
then reverse the final constructed string.
